{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\insrsid6636096\charrsid16072257 {\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid6636096 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I think you said your name was Violet May Flynn, and your present address is {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}28 Chester Street{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. Marital status, married. Could you tell me the year of your marriage please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well now then, 'cos I was over 50 when I got married. I've been married fifteen years this year, so that was 19 when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 1954 would it have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 1954 that was it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And could you tell me the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 1901.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And the birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}21 Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how many years did you live in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Let's see. We moved from there in 1918 wasn't it, so you can tell how long I was there can't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And where did you move to when you moved from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well you see then we just went into lodgings for a bit 'til this house was ready. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Till the people had got out you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 For us to come in to, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Where were the lodgings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 In {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Princes Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And were you there for a year or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well you see, yes, mother and father was there but us children, I lodged with a friend and that you see, two or three and that, 'til we 
could get this place, you see, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And in the first place why did the family move from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well the house was sold and in those days there was no Rent Act to protect your or nothing. And just the week we were moving they broug
ht in this Act, where no one was to be turned out until they could find alternative accommodation, you see. That's why we moved or mother'd never moved from there. You see the house was sold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how much notice was she given of having to move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just one week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 One week!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That's what it was in those days. You don't have to give a month now. We couldn't take it to court.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 an awful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  shock to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It 'twas. It meant breaking up the home. And of course, 'cos three children, t
here was two younger than me, we just went where we could you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So you went to friends, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your younger two? Brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I had one younger brother and one younger sister, they went. Now I think, did my brot
her stop with my mother, I don't know. But my sister went to someone in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, and that. But they're dead and gone now. But that's why. There was none of this present day system. And of course, just the week that we moved out they brought in this Act, No one to be turned out unless you found them alternative accommodation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 All that's been changed hasn't it!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And it\rquote s a good thing too
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It must have been terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was. After all they'd... and course mother didn't know nothing 
about Building Societies. I don't think there was any Building Societies in those days. But a friend of hers said, "well if I'd known I'd have lent you the money". The house went for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757685 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 200.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Goodness. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757685 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
200. And she'd have had to pay out a lot being in lodgings. And what did she do for her furniture then when she moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was all stored. One person stored it and we took a bit what we wanted and of course a lot went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you have to pay for the storage too, or was that with someone you knew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well I really and truly forget over that because it was such a shock. But I think somebody had it in a room. A friend and that, see we moved what we could and what we couldn't we had to just leave or burn and that was that. Or else we'd have still been
 in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 now. Mother'd never have moved out. 'Cos you was handy for shops and everything, but of course here it's not so handy. Well now my mother lived here, she's been dead now 27 years, as I say she died in 1942. Well she had a good many year
s of it but it's very, very cold down here, being so open and that, but there 'twas.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. So you had to all move from that house. You had the one younger brother and one younger sister. How much younger were they than you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, my brother's 65 this year, and sister'll be 61.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And do you know how old your father was when you were born? Or can you roughly estimate how old he might have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I don't know now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Is he still alive or is he dead?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Father's been dead, dad's been 
dead 27 years. If they'd a been alive they'd be an hundred odd. They were both 80 and they've been dead 27 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So he was eighty when he died was he, and that was twenty seven years ago. So I can work out from that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And so they were the same age were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Died just ten days between one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And I think you said he was a builder's labourer, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you know if he ever had any other job? Besides that, before or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 I think I'v
e heard my sister say he done a bit on the coal for a bit, you know on the coal work, but that was before my time, but then I think he was at Sim and Co for years and years and years. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Up 'til the last time of working and that, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. On the coal, do you mean mining, or delivering the coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just delivering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But he finished his working life as a builder's labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you know if he was ever out of work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Only through strikes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. He wasn't laid off in the winter months as they sometimes do in building?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. I heard my mother say, the first week they moved into Bullingdon Road, 'cos they lived in George Street, because I had one elder brother and there was an elder sister or something and the house w
asn't big enough and they moved into Bullingdon Road, and the first week they moved up there it poured of rain the whole of the week, so father never earned no money. They didn't pay wet money like they do now, see. So that was the only time, or perhaps h
e wasn't well, or through strikes, but, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Do you remember any particular strike up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. I'm almost sure there was one, I thought it was before the First World War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But I know we were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} then, 
and the strike pay was 10/- a week. 'Cos I know the next door but one neighbour, I know she gave mother a big knob of coal to have a fire and someone said to her about her "Oh, well," she said, "she's getting 10/- a week strike pay", but the rent was 7/6 
a week. So that's that. Look what they get paid now!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how long did it go on, the strike, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I was just trying to think, but I can't remember that. I can't remember, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did your mother, do you know if she ever had a job, before or after marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, taking in laundry. That's what she had to do and it was her that brought me up to do it, I'm sorry to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You don't thinks it's good work, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Hard. In those days, a pocket handkerchief a one-half d, a so
ft collar one-half d. a pair of sheets 2d, a man's right-shirt 2d, a ladies nightdress 2d, and they were long flowing ones, not the flimsy things they wear nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, they're all drip dry now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And a starched collar was only 1d, and they 
had to be polished with a polishing iron, you know these stiff collars like the men wear. You don't see those nowadays, do you, only perhaps for a dress occasion. And look at all the white shirts that had to be polished in the front. Yes, 'cos you know th
ose dress shirts had to be shiny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 How many families did she do it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well she only just did it for a friend and that. But there was someone that used to keep a restaurant in the Cornmarket that's all, down where Milwards are now, and she used to do their family washing. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But I suppose it took her quite a lot of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Of course it did. All day Monday. And of course she used to say come and help me and I used to have to stand on a chair and scrub away with the board and brush, and I've still got that board and I use it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you know, if before she married, she'd also done laundry work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. She was in service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She was in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, she was born in the country. She was born Witney way. She was in service in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Norham{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Gardens{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I heard her tell me that so I do know that. Yes that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you know where, if your father was born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, he was born in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} \{
ILLEGIBLE\} down that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your mother's washing was always done in her own home, she never had to go out at all and leave her children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And you mentioned you had an older brother and sister, so there were really six children, were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Now. My eldest brother he's dead, but let me see, there was Harry, the next one was Millie, who was Amelia really,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Are those two still living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No, both dead. Then comes my next sister, but she's still alive, she's 80 odd, then, it's very funny I was just thinking of one of my sisters if she was alive she
'd have been 79, because the Queen is 43 today isn't she, and her mother had been married nearly three years when she was born, that'll be 26}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  April, that'll be 70 and my sister died the day they were, her mother and father were married, you know the Quee
n Mother was married, I was going up to London to see the wedding. So that means that sister's 79, then there was two that died as babies with compressed measles, then there was me, and my brother and sister.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, and the oldest was a boy was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 If he were still living, how old would he be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 83 or 84.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And then the daughter that you said was really Amelia, she wasn't the one that died at the Queen's... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, that's another one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But that elder daughter how old would she have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She would have been 80, odd, 'cos that one in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Henry Street
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} is 81, and there wasn't many months between those two. But there was more of a gap between}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896  as}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
 I was the result of a new house. They always say }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 when you move house, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 don\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I haven't heard that expression.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, they always say when you move house. Once you move house then. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Now in your house in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} can you describe how many rooms it had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It had eight rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes six rooms and a big attic up the top it was one big room at the top which you could make into two, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So it had a front room did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Front room, back room, kitchen, up one flight of stairs, bedroom there, there and there, then yo
u'd got another flight of stairs to the attic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. I see, was the attic used?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. 'Cos that was our bedroom when we were children. You see, people that are in it now have turned it into a flat. Of course it was possible to do it, but of course
 we didn't, nobody didn't in those days think of all the extensions and all, like they do now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And did you ever have any relatives or any lodgers living with you in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No relatives but, I think we had one old gent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Lodging with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes, yes. Oh yes, he's dead and gone donkey's years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did your mother ever have anyone helping her with her housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No. Couldn't afford it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And the washing presumably, her own family washing, she did it at home just as she did..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
In the kitchen, you know, with the board and brush and copper, soap and soda. There was, I know when this washing powder first came out, Rinso was the first that came out. I washed a black frock and I spoilt it. I never 
heard, she said, "Your damn washing powder, just use soap, please.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did the black frock belong to the restaurant owner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, it 'twas mothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Mothers, oh dear. And did your mother or father mend or make clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. I'm afraid my father done the shoe mending.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
He cobbled in those days, and mother, yes, she used to mend everything. I was just saying today, I shall have to be like my mother, mend the sheet Not tear them up and throw them away. I'll have to me
nd them. She used to make our clothes, but of course in those days clothes weren't too expensive like, though we had to take care of them. If we had anything for Sunday it was kept for Sunday. It wasn't like you put it on for Sunday and you got it on Mond
ay and were doing your work in it, but no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was special for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did she make the clothes out of new material or from other bits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Whatever she could get hold of. And if anybody gave her anything she was grateful, and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And the shoes, were they new shoes she bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. Because as I say, there was at Butlers on Corley Road they had a shoe shop and you could get a pair of shoes for half a crown, and that, or five bob, and I know when we got a bit older there was a shop down St. Clements. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Well it's like these clubs of today where you pay weekly, you see, we always used to pay weekly there, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And then I know there was a... 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Were there just shoes, or were there clothes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, just a shoe shop that was. Then there was another gentleman down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Abingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 he was like a private house, but I suppose he turned his room in, that was I suppose direct with a wholesaler. Mother used to have a few things off him, and pay weekly because I know w
hen we all got older mother says, "Well now the children can work they must buy their own." So of course he said to mother, wouldn't any of the others, "No" she said, "They must save up and pay for it." Yes. That's how she used to get a lot of things, you
 see. So and that. Well I've heard her say the mangle and the wringer. There was a shop up St. Giles' and my elder brother used to take up half-a-crown every week for to pay it off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did he, for the mangle and the wringer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you know if there was anything else she bought on that system?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well that I don't know, because I can't remember. What they brought from the other house and it all came from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Minty's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  and those you see, so but I know she said she bought her wringer and her mangle and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you know if they charged interest, like they do on higher purchase now? Do you know if it cost her more to buy that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well, oh yes, of course, everything was dearer wasn't it. It 'twasn't like the higher purchase of today. If a thing was cash }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757685 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 5 by the time you'd paid for it it'd always worked out }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757685 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 8 or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757685 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
9. Of course it was an expensive way of buying as it is today, isn't it. But then some people have got to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Exactly. And do you know if your father helped in the house at all? If he did any household jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes when we were little he did. He used to clean the windows, and all those and he could do the painting and white-washing but he couldn't hang paper. He was a big heavy man. So he couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He couldn't hang paper, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 I can whitewash and paper. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
All this ceiling I used to do years and years ago when he was alive, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And what about things like washing up, or cleaning, did he ever give a hand with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Oh well, I expect when we were little he did, when we were all little
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But you don't actually remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. I remember I once said to him, "Mother's asked me to clean the window and he said "I did that when you were little, I'm not doing it now you're big enough to do it."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Oh yes, he helped mother a lot when we were little. Well, of course, my mother had to, at daytime, I suppose doing her laundry and that, and of course us being little, she couldn't do much, couldn't go out shopping, so wh
en father come in and had his tea he had to sit and just mind us while she went out shopping. 'Cos she said she'd often come back and found father asleep and one of us in each of his arms asleep. He never dropped us though, but that was in the other house
 though, not here, because we were all grown up then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you remember him putting you to bed, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Nothing like that. She did that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 We were always in bed when he come home from work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What time would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}
{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}Six o'clock{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That was early bed for those days, or even for today's children. It was quite early wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 My father had when he was at work, he had to be right out at Elsfield - I don't know if you know 
where Elsfield is, it's out Marston way - and he had to be over there at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}6 o'clock{\*\xmlclose}
 in the morning and he had to walk from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. By the time he come home at night he used to come in and to say to mother "Children in bed?" he used to day "Poor little devils". But we'd always come down and mother'd always left enough potatoes for him to give us one 'cos his was better'n ours we'd }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16453410\charrsid4523896 had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 at dinner time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean although you were in bed you used to come down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. We used to come down and have one of his potatoes and go back to the bedroom, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Was he the kind of father who made quite a fuss of his children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He was an affectionate father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. He thought a lot of us. He'd a sold out his last halfpenny, yes and that. He never had a lot of money, but he always... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He liked to see you when he came in? It wasn't that you had to be out of the way or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did the whole household get up early then, at about six, or was your father up on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No after, we got up at about seven. She used to make a mug of cocoa at night, mother did, and in those days it was one of those old-fashioned grates with the oven and she used to leave it in there and that was warm for him to ha
ve and he used to cut his food overnight. I can see him going it now in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. A cottage loaf in those days. He used to take the top off the cottage loaf and cut it in two, the top. And I used to say "Dad, why d'y do that?" "One's my lunch and on
e's my dinner." And he'd take it in his red handkerchief and I think I've still got it knocking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And anything else with it, or just bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Um, perhaps a bit of cheese, or a bit of bacon. He liked fat bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And so he'd get his own luncheon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well he had to have it to take that to work you see, and take a can of tea, and then when he come home he had a cooked dinner at night.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, and so did you children also have your cooked meal at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. We had it at day time. We had it at day time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So she cooked twice a day, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. Well she used to leave enough for him and warm it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, I see. Like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 My sister she's in Henry Street, now, but course as I say she's not well and she
 can't remember a thing if I tell her a thing. A little while after she'll ask me just the same question, so of course it's no good asking her anything now, 'cos she wouldn't know. But I've heard her say, when they lived in St. Clement}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16453410\charrsid4523896 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 s, she used to go al
ong, mother used to send her along, with perhaps 2d or 3d to Timms the butcher. Two-penny-worth of bullock's liver and a fat rasher for father's tea, and that. And she said I told dad once we had no dinner and he said why, and she said mother never put th
e cloth on. You see she was busy I suppose and on the side table she'd laid newspaper. My sister declared she never had her dinner, 'cos she hadn't got the table cloth on. She'd had it but the table cloth wasn't on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 You mean, when you say, she never had the dinner, she wouldn't have eaten it?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well she had her dinner, but she told father she didn't, so he said why. "Mother never put the table cloth on so how could I have had any?"

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I see what you mean, sorry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Often I slip paper on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But your mother regularly laid the cloth? Was she particular about that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. If it was only a piece of sheeting it was washed, boiled and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 starched}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 . Always the white table cloth had to be put on. Which doesn't seem, you know, a plastic one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And was she particular about how she laid the table and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. It was always laid out. Always that. Everything now and that. And she used to dish it up, not like me saucepan to plate. I don't believe in making work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh I quite agree with you. But she always had it in the dishes, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 In the serving dishes, which she served from the table then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. I can see the big joint now, being put from the oven on to the dish, and baked potatoes, and of course in those days when we lived in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 there was no gas or electric, it was oil lamp and the fire. It was a big saucepan that was put on. There was the potatoes put in a net. This is country. Potatoes put in a net, the greens 
put in, and we always had a spotted dog. Do you know what one of those are?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Is it a pudding with currants in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 With currants, sultanas, or raisins. Different every week. All in a cloth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And was it made with suet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. All put in the cloth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. All done together in the big pot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. Yes. I can still see me father lifting this big, I've still got the saucepan, down the stairs, with the handle, off though. I keep it for Christmas when I'm boiling a big piece of ham or anything.
 But those days are over now, I don't have the, I used to have my sister at Botley and her children and my brother-in-law, but not now. I can't do it now. And yes he used to lift that off and I can see him now take it off in the kitchen and skim it into t
he dishes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did she then cook the joint in the oven by itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, the meat. Sometimes we had boiled potatoes and sometimes we had baked potatoes. But it was a round of beef every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Every Sunday a round of beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 A round of beef and that was only two and an half pence a pound. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
You could get a joint for half a crown then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did she have it cold then later on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Cold on Monday. Then of course all the week we had to have what we could get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, and would she go to the butcher for meat for later in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes. 'Cos that's when we were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} she used to send me up to a butcher on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Cowley Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. 1 1/2 lb. lean stewing pieces 6d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Course we had our own vegetables 'cos father had a good allotment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Oh yes, you told me, out at Marston. Are they still where the allotments are there, because we passed the other day and I said to my husband,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, its where {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Hugh Allen Crescent{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} is. You see, you know where {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}William Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at Marston is, where the Post Office is like on the corner of 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}William Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and there's {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Foley Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Do you know where the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Somerset{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} is? The {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Somerset{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 Public House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Is that right in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No that's on the main {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Marston Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} as you're going in. Perhaps you don't go up {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Marston Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. You don't go from St. Clement}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16453410\charrsid4523896 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 s do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes I do, you go along St. Clement}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16453410\charrsid4523896 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 s and then you turn right at the top of Headington Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes that's it, yes. Turn left, 'cos there's St. Clement}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16453410\charrsid4523896 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 s Church lays back, that's where I was christened. Then straight up of course in those days there wasn't all those houses. Our allotment stand where {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Hugh Allen Crescent{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} is now and all round on that block, that's where out allotments were. And of course you used to go up 
and round to Old Marston in those days, but of course you used to go through Old Marston and that to go to Noak and Beckley and all out that way. But of course I shouldn't know it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And when he used to work on the allotments, did he go there in the summer evenings? Was that when he used to work on them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Of course when he worked wherever he was up the town he could go across, there used to be a ferry boat, before they built that bridge.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. There's still a ferry up near the Victoria Arms Inn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well may be that one or. He used to go across to the allotment and I used to take his tea up to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. In the evening. But of course Good Friday he used to be up there all day. I used to take his dinner up there an
d take his tea. That's it, he used to go in the evenings now this was a busy time for planting, wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Good Friday, yes it was the day people used to plant didn't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. He had twenty poles to do. He had a good big allotment both sides to do.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Did any of you help him with the garden. Any of your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh no, my elder brother was mostly away. My younger brother'd perhaps go up and have a bonfire, anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But not regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No father done it. And he would have no flowers. He would have no flowers on his allotment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did he feed the family with most vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well he kept us going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you ever have to buy vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
I think he kept us very nearly, we may perhaps have had to buy a bit of green stuff or anything like that but he generally grew enough. Of course I know when the runner beans came along and the peas if we had a lot he used to give them to the neighbours a
nd that. But of course I know in the First World War if we had anything over he used to give them to people and they were glad. You see. Because when there was nothing to be got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I suppose you had fresh vegetables then every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Every day, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how many days a week, do you think, you had meat? Were there some days when you had no meat at all? Or was there always something?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Perhaps when my mother was hard up and she'd only got tuppence, she'd go and get a bloater, or a herring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But would you say that most days you did have meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. Yes. We managed to have something, we never starved.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You had quite a good diet would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. Yes. We did. Even if it was only boiled rice with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 treacle}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  or jam on. You see, so we never starved. Mother'd rather go without than see us starve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did your mother sometimes go without? So that you could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well sometimes she had to cut down a bit, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did she serve herself last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And who was served first then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well I suppose she put a certain, she kept enough back for father,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Of course 'cos he wasn't there for the dinner, No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. But then as I say she was a good manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I
f we only had a bone, mother could make a dinner. She always put plenty of vegetables, onions, carrots, whatever was going, in. I can see her now turning out a good stew with a bone. We always used to say, "Wonder how she does it?"
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Had she cooked in service or had she done more housemaids jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well I think she was in the kitchen, you see. She had to do all the dirty work, pots and pans, all the grates and everything, and of course it was hard work in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes with the black lead
ing and everything. Yes. And when you, at weekends, on a Saturday I suppose your father would be out all day, he wouldn't have a half-day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. He had to go to work in the morning and then of course he'd come home at dinner time and have his bit of di
nner and perhaps go up on the allotment, or perhaps do anything in the shed. But there was no football like there is now. That's all my husband lives for, football. You see, no he was always for doing odd jobs and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Was he a sort of handyman, did he make things? Furniture and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. He didn't because he was too heavy handed. Although I've still got a couple of stools he made and everything, but, no, he couldn't make nothing Not like some of the men and that. I mean it was very rough but it lasted
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. He cobbled your shoes which saved a bit I suppose. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes he mended the shoes and all that. But no, as I say, it was hard times but we lived, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you yourself have any little jobs you had to do regularly in the home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. Every morning before I went to work. Went to school. If mother wanted any errands I had to fetch them. Yes. And I know I always had to empty the slops. There was no bathroom in the house and no toilet upstairs. The toilet was outsi
de, so of course that was my job every morning, always to do that. That was about all I had time for 'cos you had to be at school about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}half past eight{\*\xmlclose}, {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 45}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 8}}}
quarter to nine{\*\xmlclose}. But then weekends perhaps you'd have to clean the knives and forks and spoons and run errands, and do a little bit of work. Perhaps go and clean a neighbour's bricks for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean the red bricks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well the front, you know, the bricks and that. Yes clean them, with cold water, for a penny. Yes I've done it many a morning. A
 person, her husband used to put the bucket of water out before he went to work and I'd go along and clean her bricks and all that and my hands would be frozen. Crying. For a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 For a penny. Yes. But I suppose it all helped didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Well of course those days I had to pay to go to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh did you? Oh you didn't have to at all schools, did you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Well I went to Cowley St. John's Higher Grade in those days, its {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
PlaceName}}Cowley{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}St. John's{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}Secondary School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} now, isn't it. Top of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Princes Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and the opposite side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I haven't seen the school but I've heard of Cowley St. John's. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And I used to pay 4d. to go to school, and buy all my books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, and so you earned, that 1d went towards it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 That 1'd bought, with the fourpence. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 'Cos when I left the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Infants{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, mother says if you want to go to that school it's up to you. You must earn your money. I can't afford to send you there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So did you earn the whole fourpence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well I had to. If anybody give me a halfpenny I kept it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Did you save the money yourself or did your mother..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. I saved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You saved it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I saved it myself. I put it in a box.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did your mother sometimes contribute something towards it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. P
erhaps she'd buy - 'cos when I first went there I had to buy a 6 1/2d pencil box, a 6 1/2d school bag, me one-half d ruler which is downstairs, of course when you start you have to buy all books don't you. A 1/2d notebook a 6d dictionary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It's amazing how you remember all these. Why were you particularly keen to go to that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I don't know why but of course I went to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Infants
{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and it was from the Infants to the other school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But if you couldn't have afforded it you would have gone to another school would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I would've gone to the one down {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Union Street{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}East{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Council{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And you didn't want to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. I don't know why, but I thought that Cowley St. John's Higher Grade was, you know, a bit toffee nose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your younger brother and sister did they go there too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well yes. My brother when he went, he went to the Boys school after he left the Infants, and so did my sister. But of course when my sister come over there they said, oh well now there's two of you, you need only pay 3d each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh well, that was a bit easier I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes, yes. Of course I was getting, well coming on then for leaving school Well I wasn't but then I was a few years older, as she was in Standard I like,
 you see, it was Standards in those days, not Class, Standard I, you see. I can remember the Titanic going down, you know. That was 1912 wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was it I know it was roundabout then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I was in, let me see, Standard 4. In the big room, when that went down. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 
And I was just going to ask you, did your younger brother and sister, did they also do jobs in the house and earn a living. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did they have their own little jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes. Mother used to find them something to do, and th
at. I know my younger sister, there was a person opposite she used to run her errands for her.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What did she get for that do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 A halfpenny or a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That were a bit o'cake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 In a week. A week's errands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well, perhaps the person'd say, well here's a halfpenny for you today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean it was just what the person wanted to give, like a tip?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. There was no set wage then, just a halfpenny, or a penny. But I know at Christmas this person bought her a six
 and an half d doll and a six and an half d pram and I never had one. That was a thing I never had a doll and a pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you want one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well I suppose I should have liked one. Well I had a 2d wooden peg doll. You see, so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did your older brother and sisters, were they living at home then when you were first in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}? You wouldn't remember when you first went there of course, 'cos you were born there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No 'cos my elder brother when I was born, when he come home he come home from the South African War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh did he, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And he said "Mother what a thing to buy." Yes 'cos he come home, what 1901, 1902.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, after the Boer War. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes and he says to mother what a thing to buy. My elder sister was then, of course two of them were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place
}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. I don't think any of them were at home. I think they were all out in work, in service or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did they never really live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Only when I was very young. Mother used to say they used to squabble eve
n if it 'twas to nurse me. But you see having three older sisters they all wanted to nurse me. So of course I'm afraid I got spoilt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But really it was almost like two families?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes, 'cos you see there was a gap between us, you see, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. And can you remember if you had to do things for your younger brother and sister? Look after them or anything, or were they too close to you in age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. No I never done nothing for them. No, never. No, only perhaps take them out in
 the pram, or push them up and down, but no we were too close like, we all come up together like, you see, so.. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But the older ones did nurse you did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. All three used to squabble as to who got to nurse me, you see, so. But then of course they all went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} before. The two eldest went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} before they were fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Did they go into service, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And I've still got the map there, where the one in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Henley Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, when she first went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} she went to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} on a push bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Goodness all the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 On one of those old fashioned push-bikes and there's the map marked out where she'd got to go through all the towns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Wonderful. What part of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 did she go to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I don't think I've got that now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So she went through Uxbridge didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes she went through Uxbridge and all that to go to Shepherd's Bush. Let's see, of course, my aunt lived at Kensington. That was at Kensington its all round that way isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And when you say she went to your aunt, but who employed her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I don't know. I know she's worked for a lot of titled people up there, as you say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But you mean she went to your aunt and she'd gone to them from the aunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes she went to my aunt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how old would she have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Only about fourteen. Do you know how long the journey took her? As a matter of fact?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No I don't. Well I think it took her the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It would have done wouldn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It took her a day. She went through it in a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did she have to take anything with her? On the bike, or was that sent by carriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I expect so. I expect she just went up to see my aunt and to see how the land lie and perhaps when she went up there, I d
on't know if she went by bus or how she went in those days. Oh, there was no cars, trains probably or something. I don't know how she went, and that. But I know she came home, Mother was away, When the First World War broke out. She came home to look afte
r us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did she, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And I've still got the necklace she gave me the first day war broke out. The First World War, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 When she came back? From {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Well you know, she was on holiday and she come to look after us while mot
her went down in the country for; Mother was down in the country when war broke out. I can see her coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Your mother was having a holiday was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. I can see mother coming home now. Drowned. Because it was a job to catch a train, and 
that, but. No, that was it, so. And I can't. I know she was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 in service and she me, used to tell me where the places she was, matter of fact they all married and lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, those two, the two eldest girls did. Of course the eldest is dead now and the other one's down here. She came down here during the war because of the bombing, you see, because they had it very bad, round their way, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your school days? Well when you went to bed at 
about six, do you remember, you were saying, would that have been when you were at school or would that have been younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, when I was younger. 'Cos you know when you come home from school you had to do your homework didn't you, and that. But we w
ere never late going to bed. Not like the kids round the streets at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}}ten o'clock{\*\xmlclose} now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. So when you were a child of say, about nine or ten, what time would you have been in bed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well roundabout nine's quite late enough, don't you? That's when we were. We were never late, going to bed.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And did you put yourselves to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. We used to go. Mother used to perhaps come up and see and that but we were big enough to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And were you sleeping up in the attic then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. 'Cos we had, 'cos it was a big room and as I say there was three beds up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So you were all up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And the others in the family, I suppose they didn't have a bedroom, because they weren't really living at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 N
o. No. No. I know when I got older I came down and had the bedroom at the top of the stairs, you see, and that. 'Cos I know I used to have a boy friend and I used to stand at the window and see him go by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Eighteen, probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And can you tell me what room you bathed in because of course you didn't have a bathroom, like most people at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No we had to in the kitchen had to have the bath. Hot the copper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. How often would that be do you suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Once a week. Yes. Hot the copper and have the bath, and it was a big washing tray, 'cos there was no bungalow bath or anything like there is today. But I don't think that people are any cleaner, today than they were then. Matter of fact th
ey were cleaner, years ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You think so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Look at some of these scruffs that are walking about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And would it always have been the same night of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Friday. Always Friday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And would you have the clean clothes on the next day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And where did you have your family meals.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 In the back sitting room. 'T would be a room like this, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did you ever eat in the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Never once. We only had a fire in there at Christmas, like we do here now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So that room was used when? Only at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And perhaps we used to go and sit in it in the afternoon but then my mother had to work too hard all the day, she..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She wasn't one for sitting round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. What about on Sundays, did you use it then at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. We used to sit there then perhaps, probably or so, but then we had to goto Sunday School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Father used to like his sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 When on Sunday afternoons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 On Sunday afternoon. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. And the range you were telling me all about and the oven and all that, you know, where your mother used to cook, that was in the kitchen, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well there was one in the kitchen. It was one of those old-fa
shioned shut-up ranges, you know. But in the back sitting room. It was open fire-place and the oven was at the side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She had two really? Did she use both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And when did you have breakfast. Did you have that altogether in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And what sort of things did she cook? For breakfast in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Never had cooked breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You didn't have porridge?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I know the First World War when you couldn't get tea,
 I used to fill my cup with hot water and colour it with milk. When you couldn't get tea and sugar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. That must have been awful not to have had a cup of tea in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well you couldn't get it. 'Cos the First World War there was no ratio
n book, like there was when this one broke out. The ration books come out at the end of the First World War. But perhaps mother, now and again, somebody would let her have a pound of sugar 10d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. That was a lot for then wasn't it. And normally would you have bread for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes bread and butter, bread and dripping, bread and lard, which my sister called blue butter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Why did she call it blue butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I don't know. She always called it blue butter. But it was lard. I used to like bread and lard with sugar on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And so would you all sit down together? Was it like a meal or was it you just took sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No just a meal. We always sat down. We always had to get up and get ready for school, sit and have your meal. Then 
I either had to run and get the errands or do my work, which was my little odd jobs for my mother. Whatever she wanted done. That was I always had to reckon to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 empty}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  the slops and everything for her, and perhaps wash up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And on Sundays, or Saturdays, did you have anything different for breakfast? Ever have anything cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Did your mother bake her own bread, ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. You could get a loaf for two and a quarter d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It wouldn't be worth the labour would it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 At {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Butlers{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 you could get a loaf for two and a quarter d., two and an half d. delivered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did she ever make jam?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 No, because you could get a 2-lb pot of Raspberry and Gooseberry Jam for six and an half pence.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 So, you were saying, that when the jam went up to eight and an half pence she didn't buy it any more?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So did you go without jam then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 We did, or had to make it last longer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did she do anything like making pickles, or bottling fruit, vegetables, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, no. Nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She didn't do that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you ever remember her buying tinned vegetables or fruit, or dried fruit, of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 The only thing I can ever remember her buying, It was, she used to like tinned pears. She would perhaps buy a tin of pears.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 This was up to 1918, in that time was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I remember she used to buy a tin, and perhaps for a very, very, big luxury, it used to be a tin of red salmon. But you could get one of
 those tall tins for half a crown. Not what the price of it is now. She never bought nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And what about tinned meat? Did she ever buy any tinned meat? Can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember in those days, in the country are
as, a lot of men were allowed to go and snare a rabbit or something, or get a pheasant. Did your father ever supplement your meals with anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. The only rabbit we had was if our people was out in the country and they came in and brought her one or sent her one, but... 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They were her relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how often would that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Once in a blue moon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Not enough to make a difference to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Perhaps at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And was she fussy about table manners? Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well she didn't mind us talking, but we had to sit up properly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean she was fussy about elbows on the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, we all had to sit up to the table properly. We never sat round the fire with a cup of tea in one hand, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Always at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was the same true of your father, or was he allowed to sit by the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Always sat at the table. We always had our place and that was it. We had our own knife and fork and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh did you, yes. So how could you distinguish knives from each other, by the handles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well there was a different shape away, and that, and as I say, we always had our own spoon and our own cup and everything. We a
ll knew that. But perhaps if we changed a knife, but then in those days it was those old knives, wasn't it, what had to be cleaned on a board. They were very sharp though, weren't they, they had that advantage. I still use them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you, yes, they're wonderful sharp.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I have got the stainless ones but as I say, they come out high days and holidays. Because I don't like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. They don't cut nearly so well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And could you choose what you wanted to eat. I mean, did your mother let you pick and choose? From what she cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You were supposed to have something of everything, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And if you didn't want to finish what was on your plate, if you weren't hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I'm afraid we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You always did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. 'Cos the aunt that lived up in London, my cousins from the country went up to her, and I suppose they didn't like it, she kept bringing it out 'til they did eat it. She didn't throw nothing away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was that your mother's sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And was your mother the same? She liked things to be finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Mother put enough on the plate and she says when you've finished that if you want any more you can ask. It was never put on and wasted like it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And so you could ask for more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 If we wanted it, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And was she particular about how you held your knife and fork and that? Kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes we always held it properly, and as I say we were all right handed, though my father was left h
anded, but, he used to saw and cut left handed, but he used to hold his knife in his right hand. And that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And if you wanted something like the salt or the pepper you could ask for it to be passed could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And nowadays children are often allowed to bring a toy to the table, or a book, were you allowed to in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 In fact not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you all leave the table together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes unless we were fidgety and mother'd say "Well now you're finished you can get down and go out." But we daren't moved 'til she said so.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. You mean you couldn't ask to get down and then get down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And she always had a little stick and she'd only got to pick it up and we knew what that meant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Did she ever use it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. She threatened but not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did she always serve you out in the same order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes, yes, we were all coming from school together so it was, matter of fact, it was very nearly got round, 'cos you know, we were rushing in from school and rushing back, but..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You were all there I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And was your mother, when you were a child, was she the sort of mother you could tell your worries to? Were you close to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes, we all were. I think we used to, you know, tell her everything or ask her anything, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. She was an easy person to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, yes. As I say, everybody used to come to her if they wanted anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She was that helpful, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean the neighbours too used to call on her for help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. My mother always used to say "Do your neighbours a good turn but not a bad one".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did they help her with things too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes, as I say, if she wanted a
nything. But mother was very careful a I don't think she wanted for anything. What we hadn't got she went without
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. She didn't borrow?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did your parents expect you to be, how did your parents expect you to behave towards them, yo
u know, they say nowadays children are often rather rude to the grown ups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I daren't, I daren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She expected politeness always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I daren't cheek my parents.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Did you ever do so and get told off for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I tried once when I was
 getting a bit older. My father said "I'll hit you' I said "You couldn't". He says "I can hit you, and I don't want none of your cheek."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But when you were a child, a school girl, and lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, did you ever, did they ever have to punish you? Do you remember them punishing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No, no. Christmas I say, I only know my brother he had a nice new suit on, and he made it dirty, and I know mother hit him for getting his new suit dirty. And that's about the only time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 With the hand hitting you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You don't remember getting a caning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Were you ever sent to bed without your tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So you were quite well behaved children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes we had. And if she took us any-where, which was very
 rare, we used to stand there, you know stand and we never moved unless the person where we went had got children, and mother would say "Well go on, you can go out and play." But if she took us we used to stand by her and never move. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And if she went somewhere and she was talking to grown-ups, were you allowed to join in the conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. That we weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And at home did you talk to your parents when they were talking, or were you supposed to be quiet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 We only had to answer when we were spoken to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You couldn't ask them things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, but of course, as I say, they never discussed things in front of us like they do today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. You mean if they had some problem they wanted to talk about they would do it on their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
On their own, when we were either in bed or something, you see. No. No, I never heard me father or mother squabble, no. Perhaps mother'd raise her voice, like we all raise our voices, I do, but father was easy going and that. And nothing of that no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be? I mean did they have a sort of idea, like, what they thought was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. They just went on. There was no, you got to do this and you got to do that. There was nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. They weren't after you about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Of course in those days there wasn't no scholarships. I don't think there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And about manners and behaviour, though? They were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes. Oh yes. We had to behave ourselves, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And about how to behave in life in general, did they talk about that or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well in a way, but as I say we knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 From their own behaviour I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 On the question of upbringing in those days. What you\rquote 
re your parents views on swearing. You hear so much about people talking about that sort of thing with children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, of course, I know they used to have a swear now and again, which I do now. Sometimes I go it, I blind it too. I think
 it relieves your mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, I don't think it does any harm. I just wondered what their views were. They weren't fussy about that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. We didn't use it, but..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 If you had, you didn't use it yourself did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Perhaps we'd say "Oh damn it!" Something like that, but not like some of the kids of today with some of them that come out. No, oh no.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So that wasn't a problem?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your general ideas, you know, the way they brought you up. Was it sort of equally
 shared between them would you say? The kind of ideas about how to behave in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. I think we were, us younger ones, were all brought up together to behave ourselves and everything, and that. And we knew the difference between right and wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And would you say that your mother and father had an equal share in your moral instruction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. 'Cos I used to say to father, "Father can I do so and so?" "Have you asked your Mother?" I used to say "Yes." "Well it's all right then. If she 
said "yes" it's all right, but if she says "No", you're not to." Often we used to say "Yes" when we hadn't asked her and when she did find out phew!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What would she do when she found out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She'd say, "You know what you're going to get". I'd say "Yes, mother, but we won't do it again."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. So she threatened sometimes but she didn't often have to carry it out you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember in those days, did you have a birthday party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you ever get a present at a birthday or have any little thing to mark the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. It was like an ordinary day was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 An ordinary day. The only thing I can remember is at Easter. One sister that was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, every Good Friday, we had an Easter Egg, she use
d to send us an Easter Egg. If it was a chocolate one, or perhaps a marzipan one, or it was one of those eggs in those cardboard cases. We always looked for that. Every year she sent us an Easter Egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember doing anything with your father and mother on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. Just the same thing. All we got in the stocking was an orange, apple, a few nuts, a sugar pig, a sugar clock, and a 2d. pair of scales. In a big pillow case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh well, it was quite a lot, I mean, she must have had to save to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But did they have Christmas clubs then, did she pay into a club do you think for Christmas things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Course the sugar clock was only about one-half d or 1d. The little pair of scales were only 2d. -perhaps from a 1d. Bazaar or something.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Did you get together with any relatives or friends on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just kept the family to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you have any music in the house? Musical instruments, piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 We had a
 piano. The others learnt to play, but I suppose when I came along, father used to say "I want my afternoon's sleep", so he chopped it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Chopped it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Chopped the top off so the notes were in but they didn't play. I learnt to play the scales lik
e this - Doh, ray, me, see, but they didn't play. No. All the others learnt but I didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So when you were a child there was nobody playing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. You had to make your own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What about singing? Was there any singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember your parents ever playing any games? With you? Ludo or outdoor games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, I don't think so. No, perhaps us three kiddies played together you see, that was it, on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you have draughts or any games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes and Ludo and Snakes and Ladders, and my brother had all those Cigarette Cards, you know, all lined out on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And that would be in the back room would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And I'd perhaps get a cotton reel and do that French Knitting, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I know that comes out the bottom. Do they do it now? The children. I never see them do it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It's only very rare. Four tin tacks, used to go and get a halfpenny ball of that all pretty coloured wool, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did your parents themselves ever play cards or play any kind of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well they did have a bookshelf and that but they, oh yes, my father's old P.S.A's Prizes, what was they? "Ivanhoe", and all those old books. And that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. P.S.A. did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Pleasant Sunday Afternoon. It used to be at the Congregational or somewhere, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, when he was a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 A boy like, yes. He used to go, but, that was 
about the only thing. Course it was only in latter years that I've seen Mother perhaps read a book. She used to like to read some library books or something like that. But father never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He never read, no. And in those days, presumably your mother was too busy to read was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Of course she was. Of course she was, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Did she spend a lot of time on her mending in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Washing and mending and sewing, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She'd wash in the evenings too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you ever have a newspaper or a magazine? Did you have a Daily Paper or a Sunday Paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She used to have a Sunday Paper - 'The Sunday Pictorial', yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. At {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And of course, I can see on the big page "All the Titanic now sinking." The Sunday Pictorial, 2d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Were you allowed to read it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, we read it. Oh yes. 'Cos of course I was at school. In fact I was eleven when that went down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did they ever read aloud to you? Your mother or father? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Children's}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  stories, or fairy stories when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 did they tell you fairy stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Sometimes they did but very rare and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And when you were a child, do you ever remember a funeral in the family in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no. None of ours, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And when you said your mother would take you out visiting and you'd have to stand by her, who did she go and visit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Someone, one of her old friends over at Marston.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. An old friend. Was that from country days, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well I don't know how she come to know those. Of course she's dead but some of the sons and daughters are living like I am, see. I don't know how she come to know her but...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She used to go and visit her, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And what sort of time of day would she go over there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Perhaps in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Would she stay and have a meal or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No. Just go and see her. She may perhaps give her a cup of tea.
 But I know once when I went over there with her the daughter was married just had the news that her husband had been killed in the war and she was expecting her first baby. So I can remember that, you see. Yes it would be in the 1914-1918 wasn't it. Yes 
I think it was about 1917 he was killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Would that be on a weekday she'd go and visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes. She'd never go on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And did she go and visit her relations? You mentioned how she went away to the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Ah, that was her sister, she'd gone down for a holiday, right down at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Gloucester{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, Nawnton see. And that was to see her and then of course the First World War broke out then, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did she go and stop for a week or two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well she had a few days down 
there, and of course war breaking out she says, "Well I'd better get back." Yes. 'Cos it was a job. They'd taken the trains and everything off, 'cos, you know, the First World War they went mad. 'Cos there was no siren in those days. The soldier used to h
ave to stand at the street corner and blow the bugle if the zeps were coming over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Amazing. You heard that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. 'Cos I know when we was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} the person next door to us, she had two soldiers billeted on her. One came from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 his name was Richard Hoyle, and Harry Greenwood was the other, I don't know where he was. And I suppose the alarm went the chap said, "All right tell the Kaiser I'm just coming but I can't find me trousers." And I can tell you when that was, 'cos I g
ot a Birthday Book and its still upstairs and he put on it 1916, 'God made apples, God made figs, God bless Mrs. Holly for having good digs.' It's still in my book and it was 1916 he wrote that, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But your mother didn't have anyone billeted on her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And when she used to go and stay with relations, did they used to come and stay with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 My aunt never came here, did she, no. But in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}
Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} she did. Because that was years and years ago I was only little. I can just remember her coming and that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. She came to stay did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Just for a day or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What about Grandparents? Were there any Grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Dead. Dead, ever before I was thought about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. So you never had any Grandparents, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did your mother ever take you out shopping with her? Or did you mostly go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Mother'd perhaps send me shopping in the morning, but she never took us shopping, father had to mind us, at night, while she went shopping.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And what about when she, I suppose she didn't buy many readymade clothes? 'Cos she made clothes, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She made clothes. Perhaps she may buy one for something very special perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Would she take you then? Did you ever go shopping for clothes with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well she may.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But it wasn't a thing she did to take her children shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you ever remember your father taking you out anywhere without your mother, just on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, father never took us out, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you go out on family outings ever, the lot of you? With your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No we never, went out, no. The outings we only went to was the Sunday School outing when we went to Newnham by houseboat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes. And that was once a year I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, you know. The Sunday School like they have their outings, and we went on the houseboat up to Newnham. It was the only time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So on Sundays you didn't go out in the country with your parents, or anything, no?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What did your father usually do on Sundays? Have his rest did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
He had his rest. Sunday morning he used to do odd jobs perhaps. Chop all the wood for the week, look to the shoes, and go all the way round. Sunday afternoon and evening he used to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But he had a hard week didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But what about going away for a holiday, ever? I don't suppose you did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And on the Sunday you mentioned you had to go to Sunday School, would that be in the mornings when you went to School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. In the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Afternoon Sunday School, yes. And any other Sunday Services or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just the one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, that's all yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did your parents ever go to such a Church or that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And were they at all strict though about how Sundays should be kept, I mean did they worry about whether you played games or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well they never allowed us to go out and play in the streets like 
some people do. No we didn't do that. Perhaps we could play in the garden, and that, but as I say, we weren't allowed to run out Sundays.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. 'Cos we'd got our best clothes on and we had to keep them clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And then did you have a joint {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}}midday{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Because your father was home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. We had our Sunday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your father I think you mentioned had been Congregational, hadn't he, was that his denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, he was, well you see, being born down St. Barnabas, he used to go to St. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Paul's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
 in Walton Street, and St. Barnabas Church, you see. Those were his two churches when he was young. But I'm afraid after he got married and come up this end to live he forgot it. Perhaps on a Sunday afternoon he'd go to the P.S.A.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That was Congregationalist, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. That's where the Congregational was, but of course that's all pulled down now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your mother when she was a child? What was she brought up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh well, of course she went down the country church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But she had to go into service when she was eleven years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 As young as that. Amazing isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh that reminds me, I forgot to ask you to tell me about, how when she first came to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} she had to, could you tell me again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She had to walk and her father said "Keep on the main road, you see the telegraph poles, you'll know you're on the right road."
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And where was that from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Ducklington.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Ducklington, yes, and how old would she be then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, she wasn't very old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was she a teenager?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. 'Cos there wasn't much cleaning in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And can you ever remember any social activities that the Church had when you were a child? You went to the Sunday Schoo
l and you had the Newnham treat, but did you have anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No, there was nothing in those days. No they didn't give us a Christmas Party or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I did try it but, I hadn't got a voice for singing
, but then I was getting on then, I was 20 odd, when I went, you know, in the choir. Well we was in this house then, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did they have any temperance clubs when you were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street
}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well I never attended any if they did, you see, so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did your mother or father ever say grace at meals? When you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did they teach you, or did your mother teach you, to say prayers? At night when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, never. But we did, perhaps when I laid in bed I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But she didn't teach you prayers, no. What was the name of the Church when you lived in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was the parish Church, Mary St. John, but I used to go there a lot, then when we moved next door but one, they h
ad their nephew come down from Scotland for a holiday and I went to Church with him and in those days, still now I presume, the man would go one side and the woman go the other side. If you wanted to sit together you had to sit right at the back of the Ch
urch. So I turned against that. Because at the But, course, at the Cowley Fathers when I went to school the girls were always one side and the boys were the other,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 In the Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But what about, I mean, if man and wife went along, did they have to go on one side and on the other?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, they'd have to go at the back, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They went to the back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What about politics? Do you remember if your father or mother had political views when you were, you know, up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Well of course in those days it was only two, wasn't it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 
The Liberal and Labour. Um, the Liberal and Conservative. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And father was always liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 He was Liberal, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your mother, do you know if she had any views?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well, no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Do you think she would have been Conservative or Liberal?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 I think perhaps she would have been Liberal.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And do you ever remember your father voting in a General Election, going up to vote or anything? Up to 1918?
