, I suppose that was our polling station then. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes I think they used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. You don't actually remember them going to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 And do you think your father felt himself under pressure to vote Liberal. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
I mean in those days some of those people felt that if they didn't vote for a particular party it might affect their tenancy of their house or their job, or ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. It was more in the country areas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Oh yes. Oh no it didn't matter what they voted, some people never voted at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Do you know if he was ever a member of the Liberal party? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Or was he just a supporter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Just a supporter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you ever remember him working in an election, you know, going round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And would you say that he was very interested in politics or simply just that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just that way. Perhaps when it was election time he'd say "Well I suppose I'd better go out and record me vote," and that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That was about as keen as he was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes, and that. 'Cos like I know when we was here, when Frank Grey put up you know, the M.P. then, he did come to the door then and I answered it, and it was washing day and mother was in the kitchen. He says to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 me "I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  won't detain you
 I see you've got the char lady in." Mother come up and she said "I'll char lady you" she says "If you must know I'm the householder, that's my daughter." She says "Char lady." We was just doing the washing, we was just scrubbing up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It wasn't very tactful of him was it. Showed he didn't have much experience of how ordinary people lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well in those days, how old could I have been? Well it was in this house I know,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And you came here, when would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 1920 we came here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was it quite shortly after that move?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 As I say, when he was M.P. for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Oxford{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 How damn daft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I'm glad your mother said that to him anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And what did your parents, I mean, did they have any spare time activities of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They didn't go to clubs or ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No clubs, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What about your father? I mean, most men went to the pub then, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well no. He used to like a drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He liked a drink in a pub or at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well no. Of course the pubs opened at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 18}}}six o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning 'til {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 
11}}}eleven o'clock{\*\xmlclose} at night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. So would he go and have a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He'd just go and have a drink and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. After work would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well, perhaps, when he felt like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did your mother ever }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 go to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  the pub with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did she ever go with him say at the weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Well, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did she have any interest outside her home and her work would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She was a home person, was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She was a home person. She went to none of these Women's {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Union{\*\xmlclose}
, Women's Meetings, nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And do you ever remember her going out to anything to enjoy herself, up to that World War time? You know, to a cinema or music hall?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Nothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. Nothing at all, I remember when we were here she used to perhaps go to the cinema once a week, and what was that to see, Pearl White that was in the silent films, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes. And did your father take part in any sport. I remember you saying he didn't go to watch football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did he go to the races ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Nothing like that, No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Never hear him betting or anything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He didn't spend any money on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And you say they used to pay into a Boot Club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 And did they pay into sick funds, doctors' fund, or funeral or anything?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well no. 'Cos it was like, and that, it was insurance like, mother always used to, well I still goes on the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}Pearl{\*\xmlclose} like. The {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Pearl{\*\xmlclose} insurance and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She paid into that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 There was nothing in sick funds or anything, not like they are run, although of course father ..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He would have been insured as a working man wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And
 of course when we was here I know he was in the club at the Black Swan and the club at the Bullingdon. See 'cos I know I used to go every week and pay the contribution. Now that used to be like come out at Christmas didn't it, or something, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They paid the money at Christmas did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Christmas or it was like if he was sick he'd get perhaps a few shillings. That was the only thing. Nothing else. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And when you were a child in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, who did you play with in your spare time that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
I'm just trying to think. Oh lor. Well there used to be a boy or a girl down further. Who was my school pal? I never had one I don't think. No. There was further right down a girl I used to go and see and that, but she had to be indoors a
nd that was it, so we weren't out a lot. We used to have to do our playing at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean she had to be indoors by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What would that be about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It's all changed now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It is, isn't it. Wh
en we come home from school, had our tea and perhaps changed our clothes and we were allowed to go out for half an hour or so, but not to roam the streets like they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you play with your brother and sister? Did you get along well with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes. Got along well with them. I tell you we used to get the marbles out and play marbles. They were out of mother's button box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you. Yes. And where did you play? Were you allowed to play in the street, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Just in front of the house. No further.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you have any garden at the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes we had a garden, a bit of a garden, at the back that we could play in. Yes, 'cos I know my younger brother, dad made him like a truck and my sister that worked in London sh
e worked for people that got plenty of money and the children had got a toy elephant on four wheels and it stood as high as that, I could get on it, and she sent that down to him. And he harnessed that to his truck and he used to sit up for hours like thi
s, with the whip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Pretending he was driving it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. He was driving it, see. He'd sit for hours in the garden. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did your mother mind if you got dirty when you played in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 We never, oh good God, we'd never think of getting dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You never got your clothes dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Not even your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. I wore a white pinny the whole of the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean it had to last you the whole week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I used to go to school with this white pinny on, my hai
r was done back with a big bow here and this white pinny all gathered round here and a blue band all gathered round the bottom. I had a photograph taken at school and I lost it. It must have been in some books and got thrown out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But when you got home from school, did you keep that pinny on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No I took that one off and put an old one on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And the old one, did you have to wear the old one all the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. Sometimes I used to get it dirty and mother used to say "Dirty lit
tle cat", but no we took care of our clothes. Sundays when we came in "Take those clothes off and put your other ones on".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 After Sunday School, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember if your parents were particular about whom you played with or could you play with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 
Well of course in Bullingdon Road, they were, well the children were a bit refined, like now, very nice, there wasn't a great lot, so as I say, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Didn't have a problem with children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. We never had kids from all other streets. But we mostly played with ourselves in ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, in the garden. We had a hoop we ran up and down. We had our tops, whips and tops, and our diabolo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What was that I don't know that? I know whips and tops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
A diabolo, it was perhaps not so big as that, it was round both ends, narrowed in the middle and you had two sticks, with the sticks, and you do it like that, throw them up and then catch them like this all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, yes. And did you yourself as a child, did you ever get taken to a concert, or a cinema or a play? No. Nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Only one. My mother when we were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Bullingdon Road
{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, I was in next door, I suppose, perhaps playing with the kids there or something. My mother had a ticket given her to go to the theatre, and she took me to see 'The Speckled Band'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 'The Speckled Bank', what was that, a play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. It was of a family and, um, I suppose there was a girl in the family perhaps they didn't want her or something. For tw
o or three nights she said she heard a band playing and saw something speckled, and there was a box and there was a snake came out and it killed her, see. It was 'The Speckled Band', she heard the band play and the speckled thing was the snake. I can see 
it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was horrifying. No I didn't 'cos I was quite young.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It scared you did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. 'The Speckled Band'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And you didn't have any sports or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You used to earn a penny scrubbing the doorstep and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Were you ever given any pocket money, a halfpenny I think you said you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Perhaps father would give, when I took his tea, I used to say "Can I have a halfpenny please?" a
nd then I'd get a halfpennyworth of sweets coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Would it be regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. No. But I think later on he used to give us a halfpenny every Saturday. It used to be a new halfpenny, and that. That was our pocket money. Course we could spend a farthing at the time, and that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Wonderful to think of it, isn't it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, a farthing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Spanish}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  strip and keep stripping it down like this to make it go a long way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What was that called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 A Spanish strip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was it liquorice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Liquorice. One of those long thin ones, like this, and you used to pull them down like thin bootlaces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 In the area round Bullingdon Road, you were saying that the people round there were more refined.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. They were very nice 
round there then, of course, that was a very good street, but not like it is today, scruffy lot. 'Cos I was born opposite }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Benfield's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  the auctioneers, they're still there. The place is still there and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And were the people round there, were they mostly on the same sort of standard of living as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. 'Cos next door was a tailor and next door he was a printer at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 
Mowbray's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 , and that. Much all about on the building line, and very ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, in regular work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Regular work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And in those days, would you say, I mean, that, would you come into contact much with people from other walks of life? I mean, poorer or better off than yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No. P'rhaps we may meet one or two people that you know were a bit has
 up, and if mother'd got anything like what clothes we'd finished with she' give them or anything. But nothing, you know, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And what do you think in those days, do you remember your mother, I mean were you brought up to think of yourself a
s say belonging to a certain class, you know a certain..?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. We never thought we were above anybody else, used to treat them all as equals I think, and that, see. There was no class distinction like there is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 There wasn't when you were a child? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She didn't bring you up to think of yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. But of course I'm afraid I've always been the haughty one in the family. Why I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 How do you mean exactly? You mean you were particular about how you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well I know when I was at Bullingdon Road a man used to come round selling and mending umbrellas, perhaps at sixpence a time. And my sisters have told me I used to walk up and down Bullingdon Road for hours holding this umbrella up walking up and down l
ike this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean sort of fancying yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. Myself with an umbrella walking up and down. I did. Well and when came here after my sister died. That would be, well, her birthday was like it was last Saturday and then she died like a week af
ter. And I know when her funeral I had a lovely black skirt with a floating panel at the back. Oh, I thought I was it. And I wore a big straw hat, turned up brim with a veil.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Were you fond of clothes when you were a child, too, at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And I was up to latter years, but I've just gone, well ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Lost interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I think you do when you get older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. All the fashions are for teenagers now really aren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. They don't cater for me. I'm a square to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And when you were a child were you brought up to call anybody 'Sir' or 'Madam' or 'Master', in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. As long as we never called them by their Christian; we always would say, Mrs. This or Mr. That, but...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember anyone calling your mother or your father 'Sir' or 'Madam' at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. They always used to say Mrs. Hutchins, 'cos that was me name before. We used to say Mrs. Hutchins, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And were you ever told to curtsey, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That had gone out by then? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And who do you think in Oxford, when you were a child, who were considered the most important people, do you think, or would there have been certain people in the area who were considered to be sort of community leaders or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.. No. No. I don't think so. No, 'cos it was only the Mayor of Oxford and not Lord Mayor like it is today, isn't it, or nothing. No. No.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you think it's changed in rules of distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. As I say, if a Lady was worth a Lady, she used to speak to you, there was none 'oh I can't speak to you' or anything of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mean if somebody said to you, in those days, "She's a real lady", what would you have thought then? What sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well I think perhaps I thoug
ht she'd have to act as a real Lady and that, oh 'cos I heard mother say, when she was at Long Gardens in service, the person she worked for was a 'lady'. She wasn't titled but she was a 'lady she said. She was very nice and she was good to her staff and 
everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So your mother meant more that she behaved in a good way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. She treated her servants well and everything and that, and she discussed everything with them. Yes. As I say ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your mother thought that was how a 'lady' should be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Should be, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And do you think in those days it was possible to move from one social class to another? Do you remember people going up or down the social scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. I don't, know much of those you see. But of course we know years and years ago North Oxford was considered snooty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was it? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes. Oh yes. But 't isn't today. There is no nice parts in Oxford today. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And what were considered. I mean in those days you often hear people talk about some people wer
e rough and ready, you know, and others were more respectable, did you hear that distinction used when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, we used to hear what a rough and ready lot they were and that, but.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Were they some of the streets around you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Around yes, and that, but some of the streets have got more rough and ready now than when we, especially one street round there, Crown Street, Oh! That is a dilapidated street now! And that used to be ever such a nice street. Of course it's all coloured r
ound there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember seeing a policeman around, when you lived ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh my God, policemen was always around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Were they, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Not like they are today. Run a mile to find one. No, there was always, the proper old policeman, 
that used to walk along 'I am a policeman'. Old Bobby Phillips and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What did you think of him then, when you were a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 We used to look at him, and we used to say, seeing the policeman's coming we daren't do anything, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 He had his eyes all round did he? Yes. Did your mother ever say "I'll call a policeman if you're naughty" or didn't she use that expression?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No she didn't 'cos she knew, we didn't dare. She used to say "I'll have the policeman", I used to say "Yes all right". Mmm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 How do you think he treated people? The policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well, if you behaved yourself that was all right, but of course if there was a boy or two knocking about that shouldn't be, he'd give 'em a clip, he was entitled to give them a hit in
 those days, a clip round the ear 'old And they knew that meant it, you see. They knew what a policeman meant in those days, they don't today, do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And your home was rented in Bullingdon Road, you told me. Who was the landlord of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh my goodness, I don't know, an estate agent used to come and collect the money. Butlers and Ballards. I don't know who it belonged to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Whoever it was, would you say they were good landlords, and did they look after the property properly and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Father done it. He could do paper and painting and decorating, and that. I, well, course you could get a roll of paper then for two and an half d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Amazing, isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. It wasn't too bad I suppose but of course father done it all and that was that it kept it, and that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Would you say your parents had a trouble to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did they, yes. Do you remember, thinking about it, how they managed when you were a child, or was it only later on in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was only later on life as you got on that you realized.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That's always the way isn't it as you get older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Of course they never discussed. They never said, oh well we haven't got this, we haven't got that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They wouldn't talk about it, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, father'd perhaps go and see if somebody wanted a job done, to earn a shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But they never got help from outside agencies of any kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 There was none of this national assistance, I'll go and apply for this and apply for that. Nothing of that in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
You mentioned that your father, sometimes if your mother was short, they wouldn't borrow, but he would go and see if anybody had a little job to do for a shilling, or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Could you tell me how often that would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Oh not very often, unless anybody might say to him "I want a fence put up", or anything like that he'd do it, at night, after work say. But oh no, they would never borrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And he never had another job? I mean it wasn't a regular part - time job or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well he wouldn't have the time would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Just at night, if a neighbour was to say "my fence wanted just knocking up", he'd do it. Anything like that, but nothing else. Oh no. We
 had to make do with what we'd got and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And when you told me about the morning jobs you had to do, you know, helping with the errands and Miss Robson, did you carry on doing that after you left school and started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Oh, I don't kn
ow. I can't remember. No I forget. I left school the First World War and of course everything was upside down then, but I've really forgotten now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mentioned that your mother didn't think it worthwhile to make jam and things 'cos you could get them quite cheaply.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes you could then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did she ever do any home made wine making?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Nothing of that. My mother never done that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 If another child gave you a hit, you know, or slapped you, or something, and y
ou told your mother or father, what would they say to you should do?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well, she just said, "Well you fight your own battles, it's no good coming to me". But they were; the kids in those days didn't fight like the kids do now. No, we just used to play contented and that, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But if you hit back, would she feel that was the right thing to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well, she'd perhaps give me a whack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And what time in the evening did your father get home from work? I'm not sure if you mentioned that. Roughly speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 About half-past five, six o'clock, it all depended, you see, how far he'd had to come from work. 'Cos like when he had to walk right from \{
BLANK\} and all that, they used to work 'til five or half-past five then in the summer, course in the winter it was half-past four wasn't it. Like they do now, oh not like the factories, quarter past four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how many evenings in a week was he at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Every night. He never went out anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. So when he had an occasional drink in the pub, as you say, that would be during the work day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Work day, yes, perhaps you know lunch time. Yes. That was it, lunch time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And when you were a school girl, did you belong to any youth organizations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Nothing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 There was nothing of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And your free time when you were at school. Did you have any hobbies? Collect anything, or?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No. Just played, you know. What we'd got. Marbles, buttons, skipping rope, hoop-la, top, whip and top, hopscotch,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Any pets? Animals or birds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you ever go fishing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And what about a bicycle? Did you have one when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, never had a bicycle. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you take part in any sporting activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mentioned once how your mother, when your father was on strike, she got some coal from a neighbour. He gave her as a gift, you know?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, one big knob.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. How much is a knob of coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It all depends upon the size of it, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you remember her getting help from the friends or neighbours if she was ill? Was your mother ever ill at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. My mother enjoyed good health to the last.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 How lovely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Only the latter years she suffered with rheumatism, which everybody does. No. She enjoyed good health.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember, or were you too young, when your younger brother or sister was born? How she managed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You don't remember how she managed then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Oh but those days they didn't make a fuss like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well my mother just,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You mentioned she had a friend at Marston, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Just Marston, one there she used to go and see, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They didn't have sort of joint friends that they used to visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And what about your father, do you know if he had friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. They used to perhaps talk to one another up on the allotment or anything like that, but..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Not visiting? Or entertaining?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, he never went to nobody's house and nobody came to ours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was that the same with neighbours? Did neighbours not drop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. My mother said "Do your neighbour a good turn, but you don't want to be in their house and them in yours". 
That was that. She says "You tell everybody your business and then when there's a row it's all up and down street." No, but my mother was a good neighbour if anybody wanted here. If she could help them or do it she'd do it. Yes. That's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 People often tell us, well you said yourself, that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well they'd do't. They'd do't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you ever remember your parents getting together with other people and anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. They were always on their own like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. Could we get on to the school again. You told me how you went to Cowley St. John, High Grade as it was called. And it had an Infants Departs where you started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, where I started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What age were you when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 About three, or four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And when you first started did you go in the morning and in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 All day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Did you come home at dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. We all had to come home, there was no school meals then. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And the Infants was it mixed, boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And then in the other part of the school, how was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That divided then. The girls were at this one and the boys were over at top of, um, Princes Street as you know now, but of course now it
\rquote s a S
econdary School but its Church aided, see. Yes. 'Cos I found that out 'cos I asked them one day and they said yes, the Church still controlled it. Its got it on the board now, Church aided, you see, so its, still like belongs to Cowley fathers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And it was very near your home of course, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, just down Cowley Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So how long would you say it took you to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Not many minutes, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What did you think about school? Did you have any opinions about school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well I suppose it was like, sometimes you liked it and sometimes you didn't. But I suppose, oh we didn't say we didn't want to go to school. We knew we had to go and that was that. 'Cos the school board used to come round more than they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did they? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes, if you stopped away one or two days the school board was round to know why you weren't at school. What about the teachers, did you have any opinions of the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. They were all very nice. All nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you remember the things that the teachers emphasized as important. What the kind of things they were on about, you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. We just had the ordinary lessons there was nothing of that, no. But of course being a Church Scho
ol we had scripture, I don't know if schools still do today, do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, they all do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. We had the scripture and then of course whatever the morning was. Arithmetic and Geography, history and then I suppose the afternoon sewing lessons. Of course it was so many years ago, I've forgotten.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What about things like general behaviour, punctuality, tidiness, manners, were they on about that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You always had to be on time and tidy. And I know, of course, the school badge was
 an eagle, they don't have it now. They always used to like us to wear a straw boater like they do at \{BLANK\}
 and that with the band and the eagle. But you had to buy it, and of course in those days you couldn't afford, but I had an eagle on my straw hat, I do know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 That was quite unusual at that time to wear uniform, wasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Oh yes. No uniform, as long as you were clean and tidy. Yes, yes. We always had to dress, I always had a white pinny on and that, there wasn't none of this blazers l
ike they are today. And the little boys used to be in their little trousers, not these long jeans and everything, so and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you ever remember the teachers punishing you? For anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Perhaps she took a ruler out and rapped like th
at and we knew what it meant. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I don't think any of us used to stand in the corner or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. What about, did she ever use a stick? The teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes. They used
 to see what the writing was like and that, and I know I used to bring me lessons home but of course we didn't do it like they do today. But then I think when a child's been to school and supposed to be taught all day, I don't see why they want to come ho
me and do all that homework. Some of them have to bring a lot home don't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, that's true. Some of them must get very over-tired.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well I don't think that's right. As long as you've been taught. That's what you go to school for, isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well exactly, I know. It's quite a worry to some children, up quite late at night doing their homework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Then they can't get up in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So did they ever have a chance to visit the school? In those days there weren't so many open days and things were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you remember if they ever met any of your teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And the other children in the school, did they come from similar kinds of homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, they were all right. Matter of fact I still see some of them how.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Do you, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But they look at me and I look at them and I think "no I won't speak in case I'm wrong".
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did the teachers treat all the children in the same sort of way or did they single out some children for differen
t treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No pets. We used to say "Hmm, teacher's pet", but, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. There weren't some children they had a down on, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And would you say there were any cliques or gangs in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember any children who were left out of things, who were lonely boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. We all sat together in the class and we were all that..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 A nice atmosphere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, yes. Yes. There was a 'I'm a bit better than you" b
ut none of that. We were all working class in those days. Yes so there was none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Did your mother and father think of themselves as working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes they had to work and she says we're the working class, and that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And how did they decide if a person was working class or not? Would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
It was very rare they met anybody, you know, what they'd call upper classes. It was, I say, round where we lived everybody had to work and mother never went very far so, and of cour
se dad, you know, on the building line they were all matey. There was none of this "Oh, I can earn more than you", they all worked in with one another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Was there any difference between the craftsmen, the tradesmen and the labourers? In the building trade in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No I don't think so. Course none of the wages were high and there wasn't like there is now "I'm the foreman so I don't have to help you", but in those days the foreman used to go out and help the men. Bosses and all did and that, but.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you ever go to another school, or were you always at that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Always at that one. I went there and I tell you I finished there. First World War broke out August 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\super\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  didn't it. Yes August 4}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  1914 the First World War broke out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Were you at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
We were on holiday. August holidays. See we used to break up end of July and have all August. We had five weeks and two days. The two days were for St. Giles' Fair, you see. And we were on holiday when war broke out. And I went back 
September. 'Cos I had to go back to school then. And I bought all my books, 'cos every holiday like they do now, we went up a class, we call it class, it was standards in my day, Standard I and Stands II. Oh it's Forms now isn't it, Form I and Form II, I 
think. Standards. I went up into Standards and of course when we got a bit higher we perhaps done a little more. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 
Course in those days if you wanted to do anything different from what they taught you, you had to pay. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 If you wanted to learn shorthand you had to pay for that. Sewing. They }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 learnt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
 you to do ordinary sewing, you see, but if you wanted to do classic and French and all that you had to pay extra. But I know I bought a big book, I expect it was to do, to learn a bit of book keeping or something like t
hat and bought all these books and went back to school for a week or two and I as I was telling you the people next door they were a tailor and tailoress and they'd got a little girl who was a baby, and she asked mother if I could stop at home just to min
d
 Ruby for a few days while they got, 'cos they had all the orders come in for the officers' uniforms and of course they had to work hard to get them through. And it was done very nearly by hand, 'cos they didn't have a treadle machine just an ordinary tre
adle machine, 'cos I can see Mr. H \{BLANK\}
 sitting on the table with his legs crossed, you know, sewing and everything like that and I did. Mother said yes she could stop at home for a day or two, and I think I'd been at home for a week or a fortnight, when
 the School Board came to see why I wasn't at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And that was still in 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 So what did she say to the School Board then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well she told the School Board. He said, "Oh, well." He was very nice. Mother said "Can't she le
ave school?" So they went through all the books and that, as I made my attendance, and went through, and I know I left school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 'Cos I'd made my attendances at the Infants School, and I'd made my attendances at School, at the School I was. I've still got that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You were saying that you weren't fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
No. I wasn't fourteen until the January. I'd been born 1901, you see, so I know, I had a home lesson prize, the first I'd ever won from weekday school. And I know I went back at Chr
istmas to receive it. Mmm. Funny where that's gone. If anybody said, I'd say, yes, well look in the cupboard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Strange isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes I may come upon it. I shall start hunting for it now. You don't worry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you ever go to any part-time classes or education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. That was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Do you have any regrets about your schooling at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No. None at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you feel it was of benefit going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh yes, 'cos you learn to read and write. You must give 'em that. And we had to write with a pen. Not a biro.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It makes a nicer hand doesn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And you told me that while you were a school girl you used to earn this extra money, for your school fees.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, I had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And you mentioned, cleaning the doorstep, I remember. Can you think of another jobs you did that earned money? Or was it always cleaning the doorstep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No I used to clean the doorstep. Perhaps if somebody, if I ran an errand or so, they'd give me a 
halfpenny or penny, and that, and lets see, yes I used to go, there was a Mrs. Preston, I used to do that, I used to clean her bricks and it was about. Well, as I say, if I took anybody's laundry home. If it was only one person, if it was a halfpenny she'
d say, "well here you are, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 here's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896  a halfpenny", but I know I used to get fourpence to go to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Fourpence every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And that job that you had, about how many hours did it take up, when you were maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Which one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Looking after the children of the people who were doing the tailoring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12322089\charrsid4523896 Oh well, I was only perhaps in the morning probably. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
It all depended how the work went. If they weren't busy I didn't. Course I think after that. Let's see. I think after that I had a jo
b looking after children in Fairacres Road. Now lets see, my fifteenth birthday she gave me a birthday book, 'cos I remember writing in it. Writing my name.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 These were the people nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well these lived in Fairacres Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, I see. You'd gone on to them then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. I'd gone on to them, you see, and that, and I did go there from perhaps nine in the morning 'til three or so in the afternoon. Looking after two children. At least there was only one and then another one came along. But, ye
s I know that was, 'cos I remember writing in it. She didn't. Oh that was wrong. I went there just before Christmas 'cos she gave me a prayer book, 1915, and I've still got it. Yes, yes, Christmas 1915. Then for my birthday 1916, she gave me a birthday bo
o
k, but I wrote me own name in that. I wasn't, I wasn't there long. Then I left there and I went to my old Headmistress at the Infants School she lived, um, I know I was there when the First World War ended. 1918. I remember when I came home at dinner time
 I remember going up the town at night to see the celebrations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And what were you doing there exactly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Housework. Domestic work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Because she didn't have children I suppose. Teachers weren't married in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh she was married but her family, she only had a boy and a girl but they were both married you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. So you didn't look after children in her house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Housework. This and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Can I just take you back to that first job? Can you remember whether you
 worked there on a Saturday at all, with the tailors I mean? Would it sometimes be a Saturday or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Most probably it would. P'rhaps, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was fairly irregular hours was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well it was fairly and that. But I think she'd got her ol
d mother living with her as well, but, and that. But I suppose they did give me a copper or so, but it wasn't much. P'rhaps about sixpence.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It wasn't like a regular job with regular pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Your first job of that kind was the one in Fairacres Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Fairacres Road, Yes. And I forget how much they paid me a week. It wasn't much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But it was regular hours there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It was regular hours. Used to get there between half-past eight and nine and p'rhaps finish before tea you kn
ow, and that. P'rhaps if she went out in the afternoon I'd go out with her and the children and that. P'rhaps if she went round to her mother and they may p'rhaps offer me a cup of tea and they may not and I'd come home, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you go there on a Saturday, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But I don't think I went on Sundays. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. And when you got this money, you say you're not sure how much it was, do you remember if you felt it was fair or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well in those days you did. Yes. You did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you give any of it to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No. Not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And do you remember what you spent it on, or put it towards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well p'rhaps I saved it to buy clothes or anything like that. Yes. P'rhaps I had to spend a halfpenny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 How did you get on with the people you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 All right. Yes. I got on with them all right. Yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you think the employer in Fairacres Road treated you well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes. Yes. 'Cos he'd got a good job he had. But they're all dead now. I doubt even if the two children are living, and that. And that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you like the work, or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I liked it, you know. Course I suppose we're all alike we don't like it now do we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Could you tell me, did you ever think that 
you would have liked another kind of job? Was there something else you were hankering after doing? You didn't worry about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 There was nothing in those days. Only domestic work that was about the only thing going. You didn't think about being a shop assistant.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
I don't know. When did I go into a shop. Oh, I got to think, 'cos I ended my business career in a shop. It must be 1918 then I went into a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 After you left the headmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Yes that was it. I 
was there, with the headmistress and the people who used to live next door then, of course Hollies had moved, some other people was there, and I know she said "I suppose you wouldn't like to go round to the shop with my sister?" It was the dairy on Cowley
 
Road. It's gone now. I said "Mmm. Might as well, for a change." And I did. I went there. There wasn't much money but then the wages started going up then after the First World War. Of course I know the wages went up and the employer said "Well, then I can
't afford to pay you both the same wages" So I used to go from seven in the morning 'til one o'clock and the other person she lived over the shop like, she went, she came on at one 'til seven at night. I think that was it. I had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15757685 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 1 a week, and thought I was rich, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You started at that did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, that was my first job in a shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Was that more than you got at the headmistress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I should think so, see. Yes, and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 When you worked at Fairacres Road did they give you a dinner there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 They gave me a dinner. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And at the headmistress, did you get any...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes I had a dinner there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did she come home and have her dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh she'd retired then. She was old. No, she'd been retired, oh yes. She was..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you cook the dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Well first go off she hadn't retired, no. First go off, when I first went there she hadn't retired. 'Cos her and the elderly school teacher they used to come home and yes I used to get it ready and I used to cook it, but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And then did you have it with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. I never had it with them. I had to have it in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Really. That was how things were was it? Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. The maids never sat down in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. Did you remember thinking this was the wrong way of doing things or how you thought things were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And, for any job, after you finished working there in that shop, How long actually did you stay on there? In the dairy in Cowley Road?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, Lor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you ever belong to a trades union or a professional organization of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 You never did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. There was none in those days. I remember once, we were at Liptons and the fellow came in to try to get us to join a union and the 
manager said we were too busy, and that was that. We couldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you feel, I mean when the manager said that, did you feel that the employers and the workers had the same interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, we didn't in those days, not like now. You mustn't do th
is the union won't allow me and that. There was none of that. No. You had to skin a cheese, you had to get on with it. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And did you feel that between the working people there were divisions of interest? Or did you feel you were all in the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 All in one. All in one, we were. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
Yes. And do you think that when you started work it changed your attitude to life at all? Did it sort of make you different as a person at all, working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No I don't think so. I just took them as t
hey came and everything. And that. I know during the war when I was at Liptons I enjoyed myself, 'cos all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16453410\charrsid4523896 evacuees}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
 came from London, and talk about a laugh, we did used to have a good time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Of course in those days, what with the ration book. I don't know if you can remember a ration book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, well I wasn't in England then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Oh, you see, what was it, 2 oz butter, 1 oz cheese, and anything like that. And try to work that out on one book for a month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 It must have been difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 But we enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And when you started working did you spend Sunday any differently? And how long did you continue to go to Sunday School after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, yes. Yes we'd go to Sunday School.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 When you left Bullingdon Road and went into lodgings did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, we always went to Sunday School, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And when you started work did you, you didn't change your relationship with your brother and sister at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, no. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you take any interest in politics?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And did you go out in the evening when you were working as a young girl? Were you able to go out in the evening? With friends, or to do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well, perhaps now and again. There was a skating rink up on Cowley Road we used to go skating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 We used to have, and that was only 6d. We enjoyed that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And after you left school did you make any new friends, boys or girls, get to know any new people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No, no, much about the same. We all....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 All the people you'd known for a time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. And did you ever bring friends home? You mentioned that your mother and father didn't entertain in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. I never brought friends home. No. None of us did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
And did you have any special, you mentioned that you had a boyfriend you used to look out from your window to see him in the street, could you go out with a boyfriend or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Mother didn't mind as long as I was home a respectable time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. But you didn't bring him into the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Would she like to meet the people you were out with. Would she like to sort of see who they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Well she knew him. Of course he only lived up St. Mary's Road and she used to see him and talk to him and that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 She liked to know who you were with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 And was she quite strict about what time you were home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 What sort of time would she like you in by? When you were a working girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Between eight and nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6636096 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 Really, yes. And did you ever defy her on that, or did you accept it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid537132 VF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 I daren't. Unless she knew, if we'd gone to the skating rink that was different. She knew where we all were. And she'd 
come up to us. Then and th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16453410\charrsid4523896 ere}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 
\fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\langnp1033\insrsid4087917\charrsid4523896 
\par }}